---
/**
 * Responsive animated pamphlet condensing the full diabetes scrollytelling site.
 * Access at /pamphlet — use browser Print → Save as PDF.
 */
---

<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>Diabetes Pamphlet — Christian Demesa</title>
    <style>
      @import url("https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=DM+Serif+Display&family=Inter:wght@400;600;700&display=swap");

      :root {
        --green-dark: #40513b;
        --green-mid: #628141;
        --cream: #e5d9b6;
        --orange: #e67e22;
        --danger: #c0392b;
        --text: #2d2d2d;
        --bg: #fafaf5;
      }

      * {
        margin: 0;
        padding: 0;
        box-sizing: border-box;
      }

      body {
        font-family: "Inter", sans-serif;
        font-size: 1rem;
        line-height: 1.55;
        color: var(--text);
        background: var(--bg);
        -webkit-print-color-adjust: exact;
        print-color-adjust: exact;
        overflow-x: hidden;
      }

      /* ── Header ── */
      .header {
        text-align: center;
        padding: 2.5rem 1.5rem 1.5rem;
        border-bottom: 3px solid var(--green-dark);
        margin: 0 auto 1.5rem;
        max-width: 1200px;
        opacity: 0;
        transform: translateY(-30px);
        animation: slideDown 0.8s ease-out 0.2s forwards;
      }
      .header h1 {
        font-family: "DM Serif Display", serif;
        font-size: clamp(1.8rem, 5vw, 3rem);
        color: var(--green-dark);
        letter-spacing: 0.5px;
      }
      .header .byline {
        font-size: clamp(0.9rem, 2vw, 1.15rem);
        color: #777;
        margin-top: 0.25rem;
      }

      /* ── Grid ── */
      .grid {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: 1fr;
        gap: 1.25rem;
        max-width: 1200px;
        margin: 0 auto;
        padding: 0 1.25rem;
      }
      @media (min-width: 640px) {
        .grid {
          grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
        }
      }
      @media (min-width: 1024px) {
        .grid {
          grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr 1fr;
        }
      }

      /* ── Section cards ── */
      .section {
        background: white;
        border-radius: 12px;
        padding: 1.25rem 1.35rem;
        border-left: 4px solid var(--green-mid);
        box-shadow: 0 2px 12px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.06);
        /* entrance */
        opacity: 0;
        transform: translateY(40px) scale(0.97);
        /* idle float */
        transition:
          box-shadow 0.3s ease,
          transform 0.3s ease;
      }
      .section.visible {
        opacity: 1;
        transform: translateY(0) scale(1);
        animation: cardEnter 0.65s cubic-bezier(0.22, 1, 0.36, 1) forwards;
      }
      .section:hover {
        box-shadow: 0 6px 24px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
        transform: translateY(-2px) scale(1);
      }

      /* staggered idle float per card */
      .section.visible:nth-child(1) {
        animation-delay: 0s;
      }
      .section.visible:nth-child(2) {
        animation-delay: 0.1s;
      }
      .section.visible:nth-child(3) {
        animation-delay: 0.2s;
      }
      .section.visible:nth-child(4) {
        animation-delay: 0.3s;
      }
      .section.visible:nth-child(5) {
        animation-delay: 0.4s;
      }
      .section.visible:nth-child(6) {
        animation-delay: 0.5s;
      }

      /* idle breathing animation applied after entrance */
      .section.idle {
        animation: breathe 4s ease-in-out infinite;
      }
      .section.idle:nth-child(2) {
        animation-delay: 0.6s;
      }
      .section.idle:nth-child(3) {
        animation-delay: 1.2s;
      }
      .section.idle:nth-child(4) {
        animation-delay: 1.8s;
      }
      .section.idle:nth-child(5) {
        animation-delay: 2.4s;
      }
      .section.idle:nth-child(6) {
        animation-delay: 3s;
      }

      .section h2 {
        font-family: "DM Serif Display", serif;
        font-size: clamp(1.05rem, 2.5vw, 1.3rem);
        color: var(--green-dark);
        margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
        display: flex;
        align-items: center;
        gap: 0.5rem;
      }
      .section h2 .num {
        display: inline-flex;
        align-items: center;
        justify-content: center;
        width: 26px;
        height: 26px;
        background: var(--green-dark);
        color: white;
        border-radius: 50%;
        font-family: "Inter", sans-serif;
        font-size: 0.8rem;
        font-weight: 700;
        flex-shrink: 0;
      }
      .section p {
        margin-bottom: 0.45rem;
        font-size: clamp(0.875rem, 1.8vw, 1rem);
      }
      .section ul {
        padding-left: 1.25rem;
        margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
      }
      .section li {
        margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
        font-size: clamp(0.875rem, 1.8vw, 1rem);
      }

      /* ── Stat callouts ── */
      .stat {
        display: inline-block;
        background: var(--cream);
        border-radius: 4px;
        padding: 0.1em 0.45em;
        font-weight: 700;
        color: var(--green-dark);
      }
      .stat-danger {
        background: #fde8e8;
        color: var(--danger);
      }
      .stat-orange {
        background: #fef3e2;
        color: var(--orange);
      }

      /* ── Mini chart ── */
      .mini-chart {
        background: var(--cream);
        border-radius: 8px;
        padding: 0.65rem 0.75rem;
        margin: 0.6rem 0;
      }
      .mini-chart .chart-title {
        font-size: clamp(0.65rem, 1.4vw, 0.8rem);
        font-weight: 700;
        color: var(--green-dark);
        text-transform: uppercase;
        letter-spacing: 0.5px;
        margin-bottom: 0.4rem;
      }
      .bar-row {
        display: flex;
        align-items: center;
        gap: 0.5rem;
        margin-bottom: 0.3rem;
        font-size: clamp(0.75rem, 1.5vw, 0.85rem);
      }
      .bar-label {
        width: 80px;
        text-align: right;
        flex-shrink: 0;
        font-size: clamp(0.7rem, 1.4vw, 0.8rem);
      }
      .bar-track {
        flex: 1;
        height: 12px;
        background: #e8e0cc;
        border-radius: 4px;
        overflow: hidden;
      }
      .bar-fill {
        height: 100%;
        border-radius: 4px;
        width: 0%;
        transition: width 1.2s cubic-bezier(0.22, 1, 0.36, 1);
      }
      .section.visible .bar-fill {
        /* widths set via inline style, transition handles the animation */
      }
      .bar-val {
        width: 55px;
        font-weight: 700;
        font-size: clamp(0.75rem, 1.5vw, 0.85rem);
      }

      /* ── Glucose zones ── */
      .glucose-zones {
        display: flex;
        gap: 0;
        border-radius: 6px;
        overflow: hidden;
        height: 24px;
        margin: 0.5rem 0 0.35rem;
        font-size: clamp(0.6rem, 1.3vw, 0.75rem);
        font-weight: 700;
        color: white;
        text-align: center;
        line-height: 24px;
      }
      .gz-hypo {
        background: var(--danger);
        flex: 70;
      }
      .gz-normal {
        background: #27ae60;
        flex: 30;
      }
      .gz-pre {
        background: var(--orange);
        flex: 26;
      }
      .gz-diab {
        background: var(--danger);
        flex: 50;
      }

      /* idle shimmer on glucose zones */
      .section.idle .glucose-zones {
        animation: shimmer 3s ease-in-out infinite alternate;
      }

      /* ── Body complications list ── */
      .comp-grid {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
        gap: 0.25rem 0.75rem;
        font-size: clamp(0.8rem, 1.6vw, 0.9rem);
        margin: 0.35rem 0;
      }
      .comp-item {
        display: flex;
        align-items: center;
        gap: 0.35rem;
      }
      .comp-dot {
        width: 8px;
        height: 8px;
        border-radius: 50%;
        background: var(--danger);
        flex-shrink: 0;
      }
      /* idle pulse on comp dots */
      .section.idle .comp-dot {
        animation: pulse 2s ease-in-out infinite;
      }
      .section.idle .comp-item:nth-child(2) .comp-dot {
        animation-delay: 0.3s;
      }
      .section.idle .comp-item:nth-child(3) .comp-dot {
        animation-delay: 0.6s;
      }
      .section.idle .comp-item:nth-child(4) .comp-dot {
        animation-delay: 0.9s;
      }
      .section.idle .comp-item:nth-child(5) .comp-dot {
        animation-delay: 1.2s;
      }
      .section.idle .comp-item:nth-child(6) .comp-dot {
        animation-delay: 1.5s;
      }

      /* ── Plate visual ── */
      .plate {
        display: flex;
        gap: 0.4rem;
        flex-wrap: wrap;
        margin: 0.5rem 0;
      }
      .plate-item {
        background: var(--cream);
        border-radius: 6px;
        padding: 0.2rem 0.6rem;
        font-size: clamp(0.75rem, 1.5vw, 0.88rem);
        font-weight: 600;
        color: var(--green-dark);
        transition:
          transform 0.3s ease,
          background 0.3s ease;
      }
      .plate-item:hover {
        transform: scale(1.08);
        background: #d4c99a;
      }
      /* idle wobble on plate items */
      .section.idle .plate-item {
        animation: wobble 3s ease-in-out infinite;
      }
      .section.idle .plate-item:nth-child(2) {
        animation-delay: 0.4s;
      }
      .section.idle .plate-item:nth-child(3) {
        animation-delay: 0.8s;
      }
      .section.idle .plate-item:nth-child(4) {
        animation-delay: 1.2s;
      }
      .section.idle .plate-item:nth-child(5) {
        animation-delay: 1.6s;
      }
      .section.idle .plate-item:nth-child(6) {
        animation-delay: 2s;
      }

      /* ── Source lines ── */
      .source {
        font-size: clamp(0.65rem, 1.2vw, 0.75rem);
        color: #999;
        margin-top: 0.25rem;
      }

      /* ── Footer ── */
      .footer {
        max-width: 1200px;
        margin: 1.5rem auto 2rem;
        padding: 0.75rem 1.25rem 0;
        border-top: 2px solid var(--green-dark);
        display: flex;
        justify-content: space-between;
        flex-wrap: wrap;
        gap: 0.5rem;
        font-size: clamp(0.7rem, 1.3vw, 0.85rem);
        color: #888;
        opacity: 0;
        animation: fadeIn 0.8s ease-out 1.2s forwards;
      }

      /* ── Prevention callout ── */
      .prevention {
        background: linear-gradient(135deg, #e8f5e9, #f1f8e9);
        border-left-color: #27ae60;
      }

      /* ── Keyframes ── */
      @keyframes slideDown {
        to {
          opacity: 1;
          transform: translateY(0);
        }
      }
      @keyframes cardEnter {
        to {
          opacity: 1;
          transform: translateY(0) scale(1);
        }
      }
      @keyframes fadeIn {
        to {
          opacity: 1;
        }
      }
      @keyframes breathe {
        0%,
        100% {
          transform: translateY(0);
        }
        50% {
          transform: translateY(-3px);
        }
      }
      @keyframes pulse {
        0%,
        100% {
          transform: scale(1);
          opacity: 1;
        }
        50% {
          transform: scale(1.4);
          opacity: 0.7;
        }
      }
      @keyframes wobble {
        0%,
        100% {
          transform: rotate(0deg);
        }
        25% {
          transform: rotate(-1.5deg);
        }
        75% {
          transform: rotate(1.5deg);
        }
      }
      @keyframes shimmer {
        0% {
          filter: brightness(1);
        }
        100% {
          filter: brightness(1.12);
        }
      }

      /* ── Reduced motion ── */
      @media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
        *,
        *::before,
        *::after {
          animation-duration: 0.01ms !important;
          animation-iteration-count: 1 !important;
          transition-duration: 0.01ms !important;
        }
        .header,
        .section,
        .footer {
          opacity: 1;
          transform: none;
        }
      }

      /* ── Print ── */
      @media print {
        body {
          background: white;
          font-size: 8pt;
        }
        .header {
          padding: 6px 0;
          margin-bottom: 6px;
          animation: none;
          opacity: 1;
          transform: none;
        }
        .header h1 {
          font-size: 18pt;
        }
        .grid {
          grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr 1fr;
          gap: 6px;
          padding: 0;
        }
        .section {
          padding: 6px 8px;
          border-radius: 4px;
          box-shadow: none;
          opacity: 1;
          transform: none;
          animation: none;
        }
        .section p,
        .section li {
          font-size: 7pt;
        }
        .section h2 {
          font-size: 9pt;
        }
        .section h2 .num {
          width: 14px;
          height: 14px;
          font-size: 6.5pt;
        }
        .bar-row,
        .bar-label,
        .bar-val {
          font-size: 6.5pt;
        }
        .bar-track {
          height: 8px;
        }
        .mini-chart {
          padding: 4px 5px;
          margin: 3px 0;
        }
        .mini-chart .chart-title {
          font-size: 6pt;
        }
        .glucose-zones {
          height: 14px;
          font-size: 5.5pt;
          line-height: 14px;
        }
        .comp-grid {
          font-size: 6.5pt;
        }
        .comp-dot {
          width: 5px;
          height: 5px;
        }
        .plate-item {
          font-size: 6.5pt;
          padding: 1px 4px;
        }
        .source {
          font-size: 5.5pt;
        }
        .footer {
          margin-top: 5px;
          padding-top: 4px;
          font-size: 6pt;
          animation: none;
          opacity: 1;
        }
        .print-notice {
          display: none;
        }
        @page {
          size: letter;
          margin: 0.35in;
        }
      }

      /* ── Screen print notice ── */
      .print-notice {
        text-align: center;
        padding: 0.6rem 1rem;
        background: var(--cream);
        border-radius: 8px;
        margin: 0 auto 1rem;
        max-width: 1200px;
        font-size: 0.85rem;
        color: var(--green-dark);
      }
      @media print {
        .print-notice {
          display: none;
        }
      }

      /* ── Section Nav Dots ── */

      /* ── Desktop popup ── */
      .desktop-popup {
        position: fixed;
        inset: 0;
        z-index: 1000;
        display: flex;
        align-items: center;
        justify-content: center;
        background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.4);
        backdrop-filter: blur(4px);
        opacity: 0;
        pointer-events: none;
        transition: opacity 0.4s ease;
      }
      .desktop-popup.show {
        opacity: 1;
        pointer-events: auto;
      }
      .desktop-popup-card {
        background: white;
        border-radius: 16px;
        padding: 2rem 2.5rem;
        max-width: 420px;
        text-align: center;
        box-shadow: 0 20px 60px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.15);
        transform: translateY(20px) scale(0.95);
        transition: transform 0.4s cubic-bezier(0.22, 1, 0.36, 1);
      }
      .desktop-popup.show .desktop-popup-card {
        transform: translateY(0) scale(1);
      }
      .desktop-popup-title {
        font-family: "DM Serif Display", serif;
        font-size: 1.5rem;
        color: var(--green-dark);
        margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
      }
      .desktop-popup-desc {
        font-size: 0.95rem;
        color: #555;
        line-height: 1.5;
        margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
      }
      .desktop-popup-actions {
        display: flex;
        flex-direction: column;
        gap: 0.6rem;
        align-items: center;
      }
      .desktop-popup-btn {
        display: inline-block;
        background: var(--green-dark);
        color: white;
        font-weight: 600;
        font-size: 1rem;
        padding: 0.7rem 1.8rem;
        border-radius: 8px;
        text-decoration: none;
        transition:
          transform 0.2s ease,
          background 0.2s ease;
      }
      .desktop-popup-btn:hover {
        transform: scale(1.05);
        background: var(--green-mid);
      }
      .desktop-popup-dismiss {
        background: none;
        border: none;
        font-size: 0.85rem;
        color: #999;
        cursor: pointer;
        padding: 0.3rem 0.6rem;
        transition: color 0.2s ease;
      }
      .desktop-popup-dismiss:hover {
        color: var(--text);
      }
      @media print {
        .desktop-popup {
          display: none;
        }
      }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <!-- Section Nav Dots -->

    <div class="print-notice">
      <strong>To save as PDF:</strong> Press <kbd>Ctrl</kbd>+<kbd>P</kbd> (or <kbd>Cmd+P</kbd>) &rarr; Destination: "Save as PDF" &rarr; Scale: Fit to page
    </div>

    <header class="header" role="banner">
      <h1>Understanding Diabetes</h1>
      <p class="byline">by Christian Demesa</p>
    </header>

    <main class="grid" role="main">
      <!-- Section 1 -->
      <div class="section" data-section>
        <h2><span class="num">1</span> What Is Diabetes?</h2>
        <p>Your body runs on glucose — fuel for every cell. <strong>Diabetes</strong> is when blood glucose stays dangerously high because insulin isn't doing its job.</p>
        <p>
          Without glucose entering cells, your body burns fat instead, producing toxic <strong>ketone bodies</strong> that can lead to <span class="stat-danger"
            >diabetic ketoacidosis, coma, or death</span
          >.
        </p>
        <p>Diabetes is the <span class="stat">7th leading cause of death</span> in the US. Adult cases have <span class="stat">more than doubled</span> since 2001.</p>
        <div class="mini-chart">
          <div class="chart-title">US Diabetes Prevalence (adults 18+)</div>
          <div class="bar-row">
            <span class="bar-label">2001–04</span><div class="bar-track"><div class="bar-fill" data-width="74%" style="background:var(--green-mid)"></div></div><span class="bar-val">11.2%</span>
          </div>
          <div class="bar-row">
            <span class="bar-label">2009–12</span><div class="bar-track"><div class="bar-fill" data-width="80%" style="background:var(--green-mid)"></div></div><span class="bar-val">12.1%</span>
          </div>
          <div class="bar-row">
            <span class="bar-label">2015–18</span><div class="bar-track"><div class="bar-fill" data-width="94%" style="background:var(--green-dark)"></div></div><span class="bar-val">14.1%</span>
          </div>
          <div class="bar-row">
            <span class="bar-label">2021–23</span><div class="bar-track"><div class="bar-fill" data-width="90%" style="background:var(--green-dark)"></div></div><span class="bar-val">13.5%</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <p class="source">Source: CDC NHANES 2001–2023</p>
      </div>

      <!-- Section 2 -->
      <div class="section" data-section>
        <h2><span class="num">2</span> Type 1 vs. Type 2</h2>
        <p>
          <strong>Type 1</strong> — autoimmune. Your immune system destroys insulin-producing beta cells. Requires lifelong insulin. Accounts for <span class="stat">5–10%</span> of cases. Peak diagnosis
          age: <span class="stat">10 years old</span>.
        </p>
        <p><strong>Type 2</strong> — insulin resistance. Cells stop responding to insulin. Accounts for <span class="stat-orange">90–95%</span> of all cases.</p>
        <div class="mini-chart">
          <div class="chart-title">Rising Youth Incidence (annual increase)</div>
          <div class="bar-row">
            <span class="bar-label">Type 1</span><div class="bar-track"><div class="bar-fill" data-width="38%" style="background:var(--green-mid)"></div></div><span class="bar-val">+2.0%/yr</span>
          </div>
          <div class="bar-row">
            <span class="bar-label">Type 2</span><div class="bar-track"><div class="bar-fill" data-width="100%" style="background:var(--orange)"></div></div><span class="bar-val">+5.3%/yr</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <p>
          Highest increases among <strong>Asian/Pacific Islander, Hispanic,</strong> and <strong>non-Hispanic Black</strong> youth. Meanwhile, adult incidence <em>declined</em> 3.1%/yr — trends are diverging.
        </p>
        <p><strong>Prediabetes</strong> — blood glucose higher than normal but not yet diabetes. A warning sign that complications can already begin.</p>
        <p class="source">Source: SEARCH for Diabetes in Youth Study</p>
      </div>

      <!-- Section 3 -->
      <div class="section" data-section>
        <h2><span class="num">3</span> How It Develops</h2>
        <p>When you eat, sugar hits your bloodstream. Your pancreas releases insulin to help cells absorb glucose. In a healthy body, this works smoothly.</p>
        <p>But with excess sugar, inactivity, or excess weight — <strong>cells start ignoring insulin</strong>. This is insulin resistance.</p>
        <p>US overweight prevalence: <span class="stat-orange">31.1%</span>. Obesity: <span class="stat-orange">42.5%</span>.</p>
        <div class="mini-chart">
          <div class="chart-title">Screening Gap (2016–2019)</div>
          <div class="bar-row">
            <span class="bar-label">Strict testing</span><div class="bar-track"><div class="bar-fill" data-width="33%" style="background:var(--danger)"></div></div><span class="bar-val">33.4%</span>
          </div>
          <div class="bar-row">
            <span class="bar-label">Broad testing</span><div class="bar-track"><div class="bar-fill" data-width="74%" style="background:var(--orange)"></div></div><span class="bar-val">74.3%</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <p>
          At least <span class="stat-danger">1 in 4</span> overweight/obese adults went untested in 3 years. Adults <em>aware</em> of prediabetes are <span class="stat">2x more likely</span> to pursue lifestyle
          changes.
        </p>
        <p class="source">Source: CDC PCD 2023</p>
      </div>

      <!-- Section 4 -->
      <div class="section" data-section>
        <h2><span class="num">4</span> Treatment & Diet</h2>
        <p>The central goal: <strong>blood glucose control</strong>. The most powerful tool? <strong>Your plate.</strong></p>
        <div class="plate">
          <span class="plate-item">Whole grains</span>
          <span class="plate-item">Vegetables</span>
          <span class="plate-item">Fruits</span>
          <span class="plate-item">Lean protein</span>
          <span class="plate-item">Low-fat milk</span>
          <span class="plate-item">Healthy fats</span>
        </div>
        <p><strong>Why fiber matters:</strong> it slows digestion and glucose absorption, preventing blood sugar spikes.</p>
        <p><strong>Exercise</strong> helps cells use insulin more effectively — one of the most powerful interventions.</p>
        <p>Treatment spectrum: <em>lifestyle changes &rarr; oral medication &rarr; insulin injections</em>, depending on type and progression.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- Section 5 -->
      <div class="section" data-section>
        <h2><span class="num">5</span> Risks & Complications</h2>
        <p>Chronic high blood glucose damages your body over time:</p>
        <div class="comp-grid">
          <div class="comp-item"><span class="comp-dot"></span> Nerve damage & numbness</div>
          <div class="comp-item"><span class="comp-dot"></span> Eye damage & blindness</div>
          <div class="comp-item"><span class="comp-dot"></span> Poor circulation & amputation</div>
          <div class="comp-item"><span class="comp-dot"></span> Tooth & gum disease</div>
          <div class="comp-item"><span class="comp-dot"></span> Kidney failure (#1 cause)</div>
          <div class="comp-item"><span class="comp-dot"></span> Heart disease</div>
        </div>
        <div class="mini-chart">
          <div class="chart-title">Amputation Rates (per 100k patients/yr)</div>
          <div class="bar-row">
            <span class="bar-label">Women</span><div class="bar-track"><div class="bar-fill" data-width="47%" style="background:var(--orange)"></div></div><span class="bar-val">83.8</span>
          </div>
          <div class="bar-row">
            <span class="bar-label">Men</span><div class="bar-track"><div class="bar-fill" data-width="100%" style="background:var(--danger)"></div></div><span class="bar-val">178.0</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="glucose-zones">
          <div class="gz-hypo">&lt;70 Hypo</div>
          <div class="gz-normal">70–99 Normal</div>
          <div class="gz-pre">100–125 Pre</div>
          <div class="gz-diab">126+ Diabetic</div>
        </div>
        <p class="source">Source: Diabetologia meta-analysis, 2010–2020</p>
      </div>

      <!-- Section 6 -->
      <div class="section prevention" data-section>
        <h2><span class="num">6</span> Living With Diabetes</h2>
        <p>Living with diabetes isn't about deprivation — it's about <strong>balance</strong>.</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Eat regularly</strong> to balance insulin effects and avoid hypoglycemia</li>
          <li><strong>High-fiber carbs</strong>, lean proteins, unsaturated fats, low-fat dairy</li>
          <li><strong>Stay active</strong> — exercise is one of the most effective tools for glucose control</li>
          <li><strong>Monitor blood glucose</strong> consistently — control is the central goal</li>
          <li><strong>Limit sugary drinks</strong> and eat a heart-healthy, plant-based diet</li>
        </ul>
        <p style="margin-top:0.4rem"><strong>Type 2 is preventable.</strong> Lose excess weight. Exercise more. Get screened. Small changes in diet and activity can dramatically reduce your risk.</p>
        <p style="margin-top:0.4rem;font-weight:700;color:var(--green-dark)">You now know more about diabetes than most people. Share what you've learned.</p>
      </div>
    </main>

